<subSubSection lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="16" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1436,1879,2012]" lastBlockId="15.[151,1436,151,464]" lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="16" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1879,1904]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Sister to 
<emphasis box="[393,566,1880,1904]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<taxonomicName box="[393,563,1880,1904]" class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" genus="Borboropactus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Borboropactus</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
thus easily confused with it. Separated from 
<taxonomicName box="[1108,1275,1880,1904]" class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" genus="Borboropactus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1108,1275,1880,1904]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Borboropactus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and all other thomisids by the presence of two to three trichobothria on the dorsal surface of the cymbium of the male palp (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 40" captionStartId="72.[151,250,1560,1583]" captionTargetBox="[156,1431,203,1532]" captionTargetId="figure@72.[151,1436,193,1539]" captionTargetPageId="72" captionText="FIGURE 40. Scanning electron micrographs of Geraesta hirta (USNM). A – C, E – F male palp (A prolateral, B, F ventral, C, E retrolateral); D Cymbium, dorsal view. Scale bars = 100 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1049520/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
Figs 
<number box="[151,181,1951,1975]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="40.0">40</number>
</figureCitation>
D, 
<number box="[215,246,1951,1975]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="42.0">42</number>
B, 
<number box="[278,308,1951,1975]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="43.0">43</number>
C, 
<number box="[341,371,1951,1975]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="45.0">45</number>
E). Females can be separated by the presence of an epigynal lip (
<figureCitation box="[1123,1211,1951,1975]" captionStart="FIGURE 41" captionStartId="73.[151,250,1709,1732]" captionTargetBox="[159,1425,208,1677]" captionTargetId="figure@73.[151,1436,193,1688]" captionTargetPageId="73" captionText="FIGURE 41. Scanning electron micrographs of Geraesta hirta (USNM). A spinnerets; B ALS; C PMS; D PLS; E epigynum; F colulus, ventral view. Scale bars = 10 µm (B, C, F), 100 µm (A, D, E)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1049522/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
Figs 
<number box="[1183,1211,1951,1975]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="41.0">41</number>
</figureCitation>
E, 
<number box="[1244,1274,1951,1975]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="42.0">42</number>
C, 
<number box="[1307,1337,1951,1975]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="44.0">44</number>
D, 
<number box="[1371,1402,1951,1975]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="46.0">46</number>
D). Other diagnostic characters are the presence of a colulus (
<figureCitation box="[805,890,1988,2012]" captionStart="FIGURE 41" captionStartId="73.[151,250,1709,1732]" captionTargetBox="[159,1425,208,1677]" captionTargetId="figure@73.[151,1436,193,1688]" captionTargetPageId="73" captionText="FIGURE 41. Scanning electron micrographs of Geraesta hirta (USNM). A spinnerets; B ALS; C PMS; D PLS; E epigynum; F colulus, ventral view. Scale bars = 10 µm (B, C, F), 100 µm (A, D, E)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1049522/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
Figs 
<number box="[863,890,1988,2012]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="41.0">41</number>
</figureCitation>
F, 
<number box="[919,949,1988,2012]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="46.0">46</number>
E; also present in 
<taxonomicName box="[1152,1230,1988,2012]" class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" genus="Pharta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1152,1230,1988,2012]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Pharta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, separated from it by the cup-shaped MA) and the presence of a DTA (
<figureCitation box="[746,823,151,175]" captionStart="FIGURE 39" captionStartId="71.[151,250,1891,1914]" captionTargetBox="[169,1416,199,1858]" captionTargetId="figure@71.[151,1436,193,1870]" captionTargetPageId="71" captionText="FIGURE 39. Geraesta hirta (USNM). A – C male palp (A, C retrolateral, B ventral); D epigynum, ventral view; E vulva, ventral view. Scale bars = 0.1 mm (D, E), 0.2 mm (A – C)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1049518/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
Fig 
<number box="[792,823,151,175]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="39.0">39</number>
</figureCitation>
C). Separated from 
<taxonomicName box="[1044,1129,152,176]" class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" genus="Epidius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1044,1129,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Epidius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the absence of an elongated male palp tibia (tibia is longer than the cymbium in 
<taxonomicName box="[815,900,188,212]" class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" genus="Epidius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[815,900,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Epidius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; 
<figureCitation box="[916,990,188,212]" captionStart="FIGURE 35. A, B" captionStartId="67.[151,250,1947,1970]" captionTargetBox="[151,1415,195,1915]" captionTargetId="figure@67.[151,1436,193,1926]" captionTargetPageId="67" captionText="FIGURE 35. A, B Epidius typicus (SMF 4246). A epigynum, ventral view; B vulva, ventral view. C, D, E Epidius rubropictus. C right male palp, ventral view (MNHN 22347); D – E female from Sumatra (D epigynum, ventral view, E vulva, ventral view). Scale bars = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1049510/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
Fig 
<number box="[962,990,188,212]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="35.0">35</number>
</figureCitation>
C) and the absence of 
<number box="[1247,1313,188,212]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="5.0" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="4.0">4 to 6</number>
thick long spines on the distal margin of the tibia of the male palp (
<figureCitation box="[787,874,223,247]" captionStart="FIGURE 33" captionStartId="65.[151,250,1983,2006]" captionTargetBox="[205,1378,176,1961]" captionTargetId="figure@65.[174,1418,173,1962]" captionTargetPageId="65" captionText="FIGURE 33. Epidius binotatus (MNHN 13670 / 1574). A ventral view of left male palp. B, C Epidius binotatus guineensis (MRAC 122567), right male palp (B ventral, C retrolateral). Scale bars = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1049506/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
Figs 
<number box="[844,874,223,247]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="33.0">33</number>
</figureCitation>
B, 
<number box="[906,935,223,247]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="35.0">35</number>
C, 
<number box="[967,998,223,247]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="36.0">36</number>
B). Separated from 
<taxonomicName box="[1217,1359,224,248]" class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" genus="Cebrenninus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1217,1359,224,248]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Cebrenninus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the presence of a free embolus that originates at the center of the bulb; and the presence of a SDT inward turn in the male palp in 
<taxonomicName box="[294,436,296,320]" class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" genus="Cebrenninus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[294,436,296,320]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Cebrenninus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[450,535,295,319]" captionStart="FIGURE 27" captionStartId="59.[151,250,1947,1970]" captionTargetBox="[153,1428,181,1923]" captionTargetId="figure@59.[151,1436,169,1926]" captionTargetPageId="59" captionText="FIGURE 27. Cebrenninus rugosus. A, B male from Thailand (MHNG), left palp (A ventral, B retrolateral); C male palp, retrolateral view (lectotype MNHN 8652 / 1572); D, E female from Thailand (D epigynum, ventral view, E vulva, dorsal view). Scale bars = 0.1 mm (E, D) 0.2 mm (C), 0.5 mm (A, B)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1049492/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
Figs 
<number box="[506,535,295,319]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="27.0">27</number>
</figureCitation>
A, 
<number box="[568,598,295,319]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="30.0">30</number>
A). Females can be separated from those of 
<taxonomicName box="[1085,1227,296,320]" class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" genus="Cebrenninus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1085,1227,296,320]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Cebrenninus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the presence of large globular spermathecae that lack CD in the latter genus (
<figureCitation box="[836,924,332,356]" captionStart="FIGURE 30" captionStartId="62.[151,250,1977,2000]" captionTargetBox="[168,1420,188,1964]" captionTargetId="figure@62.[151,1436,181,1970]" captionTargetPageId="62" captionText="FIGURE 30. Cebrenninus srivijaya sp. nov., male holotype and female paratype from Sumatra (MHNG). A, B male palp (A ventral, B retrolateral); C epigynum, ventral view; D – E vulva (D ventral, E dorsal). Scale bars = 0.1 mm (C – E), 0.2 mm (A, B)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1049496/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
Figs 
<number box="[893,924,332,356]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="30.0">30</number>
</figureCitation>
D).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1059,367,392]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" type="distribution">
